<task id="task_E0C11EE79DAD4FE89D7FD62B679BEE7F">
  <title>Add Mboxes to a Campaign with Onsite</title>
  <shortdesc>You can use Onsite to browse for mboxes on your site, so you can
	 choose one for your campaign when creating or editing a campaign. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context_CABC748AA3514BC5B8426FC4E19F7F8C">
      <p>To browse for mboxes: 
		</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_534DB87619A54416A3E23722D1514AFF">
      <step id="step_9B5817CC264045C6836D7458326A8451">
        <cmd>Select Browse for mboxes from the mbox select dropdown box on the
			 campaign edit page to open Onsite in a different browser window. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_FE5656B464D64FBE866C1313218CC262">
        <cmd>In the new browser window, surf to the appropriate page (or enter
			 a url manually). 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>Each mbox on your page is highlighted with a gray overlay. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_556F80E7BD8348B7AA2AE46587461114">
        <cmd>Click the desired mbox area to select that mbox for the campaign. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>Once the mbox is selected, Onsite closes and you return to the
				campaign edit page with that mbox selected in the dropdown. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
